<p>After installing <strong>OS X El Capitan</strong> (10.11) my ruby <em>compass</em> is no longer working. After trying to install <em>compass</em> I recieve error message like this:</p>  <pre><code>$ sudo gem install compass   ERROR:  While executing gem ... (Errno::EPERM)       Operation not permitted - /usr/bin/compass </code></pre>  <p>The fix I found was simply to put the PATH in the install command for any ruby gem package:</p>  <pre><code>$  sudo gem install -n /usr/local/bin GEM_PACKAGE_NAME </code></pre>  <p>So with <em>compass</em> it worked for me as:</p>  <pre><code>$ sudo gem install -n /usr/local/bin compass </code></pre>  <p>Good Luck!</p>